lib/Probability/Kernel/Composition/MapComap.html#ProbabilityTheory.Kernel.map\">map</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">ω</span> : <span class=\"fn\">Ω</span>) =&gt; <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">(</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">ω</span></span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">ω</span></span><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod.mk\">)</a></span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a>     <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">μ</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Trim.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.trim\">trim</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">hm'</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Kernel/Composition/MeasureCompProd.html#MeasureTheory.Measure.compProd\">compProd</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Kernel/Condexp.html#ProbabilityTheory.condExpKernel\">condExpKernel</a> <span class=\"fn\">μ</span> <span class=\"fn\">m'</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Kernel/Composition/MapComap.html#ProbabilityTheory.Kernel.map\">map</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">f</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Kernel/Composition/Prod.html#ProbabilityTheory.Kernel.prod\">prod</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Kernel/Condexp.html#ProbabilityTheory.condExpKernel\">condExpKernel</a> <span class=\"fn\">μ</span> <span class=\"fn\">m'</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Kernel/Composition/MapComap.html#ProbabilityTheory.Kernel.map\">map</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">g</span>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Two random variables are conditionally independent iff they satisfy the almost sure equality\nof conditional expectations `μ⟦f ⁻¹' s ∩ g ⁻¹' t | m'⟧ =ᵐ[μ] μ⟦f ⁻¹' s | m'⟧ * μ⟦g ⁻¹' t | m'⟧`\nfor all measurable sets `s` and `t` (see `condIndepFun_iff_condExp_inter_preimage_eq_mul`).\nHere, this is phrased with Markov kernels associated to the conditional expectations, and the\nalmost sure equality is expressed as equality of the composition-product with the measure, which is\nequivalent to a.e. equality. See `condIndepFun_iff_map_prod_eq_prod_map_map` for the a.e. equality\nversion with kernels.\n\nFor a random variable `f`, `(condExpKernel μ m').map f` is the law of the conditional expectation\nof `f` given `m'`: almost surely, `(condExpKernel μ m').map f ω s = μ⟦f ⁻¹' s | m'⟧ ω`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Probability/Independence/Conditional.html#ProbabilityTheory.condIndepFun_iff_compProd_map_prod_eq_compProd_prod_map_map","kind":"theorem","line":763,"name":"ProbabilityTheory.condIndepFun_iff_compProd_map_prod_eq_compProd_prod_map_map","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Probability/Independence/Conditional.lean#L763-L778"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Probability/Independence/Conditional.html#ProbabilityTheory.condIndepFun_self_right\"><span class=\"name\">ProbabilityTheory</span>.<span class=\"name\">condIndepFun_self_right</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">Ω</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">β'</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_ar